<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{kotoninaru}}}} indicates an event or decision that occurs irrespective of the speaker's volition.
The focus is on the action that happens.
It differs from <a href="grammar-koto-ni-suru.html">@HI{{kotonisuru}}</a>, which marks a volitional decision.


<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{come^year^large^heights}}ni@KJ{{revolve^diligence}}suru@EM{{kotoninarimashita}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It has been decided that next year I will transfer to Osaka.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
This construction can be used even if the experiencer chooses to do something as it sounds more indirect than simply stating directly that
the experiencer has made a decision and so is considered to be more polite. Compare with <a href="grammar-koto-ni-suru.html">@HI{{kotonisuru}}</a>.
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="te-iru">Using</a> @HI{{@EM{{kotoninatteiru}}}} shows that a decision took place at some point in the past and its results are still in effect. It may go so
far as to indicate that something has become a rule or a custom.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now^day}}@FG{{@KJ{{mountain^rice*field}}:yamada}}@KJ{{before^life}}ni@KJ{{meeting}}u@EM{{kotoninatteimasu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Today (it has been arranged that) I'm seeing Professor Yamada.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{kotoninaru}}}} can be a phrase that indicates that an action or event leads to a certain situation or conclusion.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now}}zorewoshiteokanakattara@FG{{@KJ{{behind}}:ato}}de@FG{{@KJ{{large^unusual}}:taihen'}}na@EM{{kotoninaru}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      If we don't do this now, we will end up with an awful situation later.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

